15\le(3+\sin^2x)(4+\cos^2x)\le16 \mbox{ for any }x \in \mathbb{R}
\sin
 (3 + \sin^2 x)(4+\cos^2 x) = 12 + 3\cos^2 x + 4\sin^2 x + \sin^2 x \cos^2 x 
\sin^2 x + \cos^2 x = 1
 15 + \sin^2x + \sin^2 x\cos^2 x
 0 \leq \sin^2 x + \sin^2 x \cos^2 x \leq 1
 (1-\cos^2 x) + \sin^2 x \cos^2 x = 1+ \cos^2 x(\sin^2x -1) = 1-\cos^4 x.
0\leq \cos^4 x \leq 1
 (3+\sin^2 x)(4+\cos^2 x) = (3 + (1-\cos^2 x))(4+\cos^2 x) 
 = (4-\cos^2 x)(4+\cos^2 x) = 16 - \cos^4 x
